09/04/2004
SOUFLI, Greece -- Five army conscripts died Thursday (8 April) morning at a military outpost near Soufli, in the Evros border region. 
The soldiers hit a live wire while trying to erect a flagpole that reportedly had blown down the night before. 
Greek President Costas Stephanopoulos expressed his grief over the tragedy and dispatched Defence Minister Spilios Spiliotopopoulos to the site to investigate the circumstances of the accident. 
(Kathimerini - 09/04/04; ANA, MPA - 08/04/04)
